This paper deals with the problem of removing rain streaks from images, which is a common task in computer vision. The proposed method uses a deep learning approach, which is often studied in the computer vision subfield (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing datasets and proposes a new dataset, which involves data collection and processing, and can be considered as a data-driven approach, which is often studied in the machine learning subfield (cs.LG). The proposed method also involves attention mechanisms, which are often studied in the artificial intelligence subfield (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of modeling real rain characteristics, which can be considered as a graphics subfield (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations, which can be considered as a multimedia subfield (cs.MM).
